⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Elena
node M1 · M1 · ⟦Elena:M1:ab57a1⟧

WHO   — Elena — First Queen of Adarlan · the dead who walks
WHAT  — A ghost-queen and guide — the buried conscience of the castle, who marks a chosen champion with protection and binds her to an old, half-forgotten war against a rising evil.
WHERE — M1 · Maas  Framework inputs: Throne of Glass — book one  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because some debts outlast death; because a kingdom built on a queen's grave should not fall to the same darkness she once helped bind; because evil left unwatched will rise again, and the dead remember what the living have forgotten.
HOW   — By appearing to Celaena in dream and vision, by laying a healing, protecting mark upon her, by setting her the task of finding the source of the murders and defeating the evil in the castle — and by the deep, hidden magic of the Wyrdmarks.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I have slept long beneath this castle — but I am not done, and neither are you.

